  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Hamkor Bank SL</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) Enable the bank to increase access to finance for MSMEs, largely in remote and rural areas of Uzbekistan, and thus, contribute to employment generation and overall economic development.   2) Build market confidence for other investors to engage with Hamkorbank and the private sector of Uzbekistan on a long-term basis.  3) Promote best banking practices in risk management, E&amp;S, insurance, AML throughout the banking sector and regulations of Uzbekistan by working with Hamkorbank</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project involves a senior loan of up to US$7.5 million to Open Joint Stock Commercial Bank Hamkorbank (Hamkorbank or the Bank). Hamkorbank is a middle-sized private regional bank in Uzbekistan. Its core activities include offering MSME loans, consumer loans, leasing, and trade finance products. IFCs investment would enable the Bank to expand the scope of its lending program to MSMEs, with main focus on remote areas, which is well aligned with IFCs financial markets strategy for Uzbekistan.</narrative>
  </description>
